The medical bed market is witnessing significant growth driven by factors such as the increasing prevalence of chronic diseases, the growing aging population, and the rise in healthcare expenditure globally. Hospitals continue to be the major end users of medical beds due to the high demand for inpatient care services. The shift towards home care settings is also driving market growth, as more patients prefer to receive care in the comfort of their homes, leading to an increased demand for medical beds in these settings.

In terms of product type segmentation, electric beds are gaining traction in the market due to their advanced features that offer enhanced patient comfort and caregiver convenience. The trend towards semi-electric and electric beds is expected to continue as healthcare facilities seek more efficient and technologically advanced solutions to meet the needs of patients.

